# Interview Practice App (115.md)

This project is the **Interview Practice app** from the task in `115.md`. The app lives in this repo root (no separate app subfolder). When suggesting or modifying code, align with the task requirements and chosen stack.

## Interview prep focus

**Technical:** coding questions, system design, algorithms. The app helps users practise for technical interviews (not behavioural or other domains unless extended later).

## Tech stack

- **Front-end:** Next.js (JavaScript). Single-page app.
- **Back-end / API:** OpenAI API. Use one of: GPT-4.1, GPT-4.1 mini, GPT-4.1 nano, GPT-4o, GPT-4o mini.

## Required (from 115.md)

1. Call the OpenAI API with the chosen model.
2. **At least 5 system prompts** using different techniques (e.g. few-shot, Chain-of-Thought, zero-shot). Compare and use what works best.
3. **Tune at least one OpenAI setting** (temperature, top_p, frequency_penalty, etc.).
4. **At least one security guard** to prevent misuse (e.g. input validation, prompt validation, rate limits).

